A six-year-old boy Marvelous Heness stolen by traffickers has been found and reunited with his parents in Abia State. The boy was stolen from his parents’ Port Harcourt, Rivers State home and was with his abductors for two months before he was rescued with the help of the Abia State government. In Umuahia, during his handover, Commissioner for Women Affairs and Social Development, Mrs. Ukachi Amala said the boy’s rescue was miraculous. Amid tears of joy, the boy’s parents recalled how their son was taken away from their home.